ActIndian Act
SubjectEagle Village First Nation - Kipawa Indian Reserve ** Confirmation **
PrecisOrder confirming that the lands consisting of 29.686 hectares (73.356 acres), excluding mines and minerals, were set apart as reserve on February 29, 2008, and continue to be set apart as reserve for the use and benefit of the EAGLE VILLAGE FIRST NATION - KIPAWA BAND. The lands are contiguous to the main site of the reserve which is located in the Abitibi-Témiscamingue federal district, 10 kilometres west of Témiscaming on Lake Kipawa, in Quebec.
